latestPosts.caption:
14 months postpartum.
I started this journey at around 52–54 kg and reached 76 kg in my third trimester with Ottis. Since then, I’ve chosen to focus on healing before even thinking about the gym.

In those early months—between breastfeeding, caring for Ottis full-time, and Rawky and I doing it all on our own—there simply wasn’t space to prioritize myself.

Gradually, the weight has been coming off naturally. What’s left now are those stubborn bits that have settled in over time. Maybe now, with a little more support and rhythm in place, I can finally carve out that time—for movement, for strength, and for me.

One step at a time.

Where are you at in your postpartum journey? 
#14MonthsPostpartum #HealingAfterBirth #PostpartumBody #PostpartumRecovery #SlowAndSteadyHealing #MotherhoodUnfiltered #MyHealingSeason #MakingSpaceForMe

Turns out motherhood fits into the feed just fine 🤍

p.s If you see me posting, just know the baby finally napped ✌🏽
